            <fr:title text="Subspaces">Subspaces</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> of a <fr:link href="/forest/0003/" title="Elementary Vector Space" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/0003/" display-uri="0003" type="local">vector space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {V}]]></fr:tex>, is a <html:em>subspace</html:em> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is also a vector space with the same additive identity, addition, and scalar multiplication as on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>In practice to check if a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {V}]]></fr:tex> is a subspace one must check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> satisfies:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li><html:p><html:strong>Additive Identity</html:strong> <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[0\in  U]]></fr:tex></html:p></html:li>
  <html:li><html:p><html:strong>Closure Under Addition</html:strong> <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[u,w \in  U\rightarrow  u+w\in  U]]></fr:tex></html:p></html:li>
  <html:li><html:p><html:strong>Closure Under Scalar Multiplication</html:strong> <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[a\in \mathbb {F} \land  u\in  U\rightarrow  au\in  U]]></fr:tex></html:p></html:li></html:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
